<div class="patternContent"><div class="patternTopic"> For WLCG sites, the <span class="twikiNewLink">SI2K<a href="/bin/edit/InformationServices/SI2K?topicparent=InformationServices.GipSi2k" rel="nofollow" title="SI2K (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> value for each of your subclusters is a very delicate subject.  Because incorrect <span class="twikiNewLink">SI2K<a href="/bin/edit/InformationServices/SI2K?topicparent=InformationServices.GipSi2k" rel="nofollow" title="SI2K (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> scores can lead to incorrect pledge contribution data for the WLCG, some sites want to set their own <span class="twikiNewLink">SI2K<a href="/bin/edit/InformationServices/SI2K?topicparent=InformationServices.GipSi2k" rel="nofollow" title="SI2K (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> values instead of using the ones determined centrally.
<p />
To do this, we will edit the following file (OSG 0.8.0):
<p />
<pre>
$VDT&#95;LOCATION/lcg/etc/alter-attributes.conf
</pre>
<p />
For OSG 0.9.0 and OSG 1.0.0:
<p />
<pre>
$VDT&#95;LOCATION/gip/etc/alter-attributes.conf
</pre>
<p />
Determine the DN of the subcluster you want to edit.  You can find your GIP data here:
<p />
<a href="http://is.grid.iu.edu/cgi-bin/status.cgi" target="_top">http://is.grid.iu.edu/cgi-bin/status.cgi</a>
<p />
For example, MWT2_UC will want to look here:
<p />
<a href="http://is.grid.iu.edu/cgi-bin/show_source_data?which=MWT2_UC&amp;source=served" target="_top">http://is.grid.iu.edu/cgi-bin/show_source_data?which=MWT2_UC&amp;source=served</a>
<p />
Search through the data for the word "Subcluster".  Here's a sample DN for a subcluster of MWT2_UC which we will use for the example:
<p />
<pre>
dn: GlueSubClusterUniqueID&#61;uct2-grid6,GlueClusterUniqueID&#61;uct2-grid6.uchicago.edu,mds-vo-name&#61;MWT2&#95;UC,o&#61;grid
</pre>
<p />
When we change this DN in the GIP, we will replace the above mds-vo-name with <code>mds-vo-name=local</code>.
<p />
Now, edit the <code>GlueHostBenchmarkSI00</code> attribute.  The full entry in <code>alter-attributes.conf</code> is now:
<p />
<pre>
dn: GlueSubClusterUniqueID&#61;uct2-grid6,GlueClusterUniqueID&#61;uct2-grid6.uchicago.edu,mds-vo-name&#61;local,o&#61;grid
GlueHostBenchmarkSI00: 1700
</pre>
<p />
If you will blindly copy/paste the above entry, make sure you update the value for <span class="twikiNewLink">SubClusterUniqueID<a href="/bin/edit/InformationServices/SubClusterUniqueID?topicparent=InformationServices.GipSi2k" rel="nofollow" title="SubClusterUniqueID (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span>, <span class="twikiNewLink">ClusterUniqueID<a href="/bin/edit/InformationServices/ClusterUniqueID?topicparent=InformationServices.GipSi2k" rel="nofollow" title="ClusterUniqueID (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span>, and mds-vo-name (in addition to the new <span class="twikiNewLink">SI2K<a href="/bin/edit/InformationServices/SI2K?topicparent=InformationServices.GipSi2k" rel="nofollow" title="SI2K (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> value).
<p />
The <span class="twikiNewLink">SI2K<a href="/bin/edit/InformationServices/SI2K?topicparent=InformationServices.GipSi2k" rel="nofollow" title="SI2K (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> value should be <strong>per core</strong>, not per machine.  Do a sanity check; a Pentium III has a <span class="twikiNewLink">SI2K<a href="/bin/edit/InformationServices/SI2K?topicparent=InformationServices.GipSi2k" rel="nofollow" title="SI2K (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> of around 400.  The newest (May 2008) Intel Xeons score around 4000.  Your scores should be somewhere in between.
<p />
The GIP data will take about 20 minutes to propagate to the GOC BDII.  <a href="http://t2.unl.edu/gratia/wlcg_reporting" target="_top">The WLCG pledge webpage</a> updates it's information 3 times a day, so make sure the new subcluster values are reflected the next day.
<p />
-- <a href="/bin/view/Main/BrianBockelman" class="twikiLink">BrianBockelman</a> - 29 Apr 2008</div><!-- /patternTopic-->
